---
import PageLayout from '../../layouts/PageLayout.astro';
import CTA from '../../components/sections/CTA.astro';
---

<PageLayout
  title="Reporting & Visibility"
  description="Cinturon360 delivers real-time, finance-grade reporting for travel programs. Spend visibility by segment, department, and cost centre — CFO-ready, not Excel-ready."
>
  <div class="pt-32 pb-16" style="background: var(--c360-dark);">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 max-w-7xl">
      <div class="max-w-3xl">
        <span class="section-badge section-badge-primary mb-4">Platform — Reporting & Visibility</span>
        <h1 class="font-heading text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-white mb-6">
          Finance-grade reporting. Not another Excel export.
        </h1>
        <p class="text-xl leading-relaxed" style="color: rgba(248,250,252,0.55);">
          Real-time spend visibility across every booking, approval, exception, and policy outcome — structured for finance teams, compliance review, and client reporting. Available immediately. Not at month end.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Problem -->
  <section class="section bg-white">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 max-w-7xl">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mb-12">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-xs font-medium bg-orange-100 text-orange-700 mb-4">
          The problem
        </span>
        <h2 class="font-heading text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-4">
          Travel reporting is still manual work
        </h2>
        <p class="text-slate-600 text-lg leading-relaxed mb-4">
          Someone in the team spends two days every month pulling booking data from a GDS export, cross-referencing it against an approval log in a spreadsheet, and producing a report that's already out of date by the time it reaches finance.
        </p>
        <p class="text-slate-600 text-lg leading-relaxed">
          The data exists. The problem is that it's fragmented across booking tools, approval email threads, and expense systems — with no single source of truth.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-start">
        <div>
          <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-6">What <span style="color: var(--c360-primary);">Cinturon</span><span style="color: var(--c360-accent);">360</span> delivers</h2>
          <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
            Booking, approval, and policy outcome data is captured in a single data model — so reporting doesn't require aggregation. Spend is visible in real time, segmented however the viewer needs it, and exportable in structured formats for finance, audit, or client review.
          </p>
          <div class="space-y-3">
            {[
              'Real-time spend visibility — not month-end summaries',
              'Breakdown by traveller, department, cost centre, segment',
              'Policy compliance rate and exception analysis',
              'Approval turnaround time and escalation metrics',
              'Supplier and route spend analysis',
              'Multi-entity consolidation for complex programs',
              'Export-ready: structured data, not raw dumps',
              'Client-facing reporting for TMC account management',
            ].map((item) => (
              <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <span class="mt-1 w-5 h-5 rounded-full bg-emerald-100 flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">
                  <svg class="w-3 h-3 text-emerald-600" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
                    <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
                  </svg>
                </span>
                <span class="text-sm text-slate-700">{item}</span>
              </div>
            ))}
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="space-y-6">
          <div class="p-6 bg-emerald-50 rounded-2xl border border-emerald-100">
            <h3 class="font-heading text-lg font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2">For finance teams</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">
              CFO-ready spend data with cost centre allocation, budget tracking, and variance analysis. Travel spend is treated like any other managed cost — structured, attributed, and reviewable without manual assembly.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="p-6 bg-sky-50 rounded-2xl border border-sky-100">
            <h3 class="font-heading text-lg font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2">For TMC account managers</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">
              Client-facing reporting without the monthly export ritual. Account managers can pull current spend, compliance, and exception data at any time — making client reviews a conversation, not a presentation of last month's news.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="p-6 bg-slate-50 rounded-2xl border border-slate-100">
            <h3 class="font-heading text-lg font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2">For audit and compliance</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">
              Every booking decision, approval, and exception is recorded with context. Compliance reports are generated from the same data that drives operations — no reconstruction, no interpretation.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <CTA
    title="Visibility that doesn't require a spreadsheet."
    description="Talk to the team about what finance-grade reporting looks like for your travel program."
    primaryCTA={{ label: 'Book a Conversation', href: '/contact' }}
    secondaryCTA={{ label: 'Back to Platform', href: '/' }}
  />
</PageLayout>
